{
  "stem": "19895.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 16.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he always believed in traditional Jewish customs, that when something big happens, a father blesses his child.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SOBBING] So [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I just very humbly bent my head.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Father put his hand out and said the traditional Jewish prayer, [HEBREW], be blessed, and-- be blessed by God.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then he said to the other gentleman, who was the father of this boy, Stern, Tomas-- Tomas Stern, who was my friend.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father said the two of you, hold hands and never let sight of each other.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Try to help each other, whatever will be.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then he said to the other man, he says, bless your child.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He says, I don't know the prayer.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He says, say it after me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they went.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's the beginning of the death march, which is called the death march.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was from Budapest to the Austrian border.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Quite a distance, no food, no transportation-- on your feet.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had to cover a day as much as, as much as [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] 15, 20 miles.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And disorderly herd of [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] people, age 16 till 45, some of the people sick.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Pretty soon, after a day or two, some of them just collapsed-- from exhaustion, from starvation, from their sickness-- and died.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Some of them didn't die.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then people who had some money with them on the highway were trying to help.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And somehow, some-- I don't know how they got hold of a, a, a carriage-- not a horse-drawn carriage, just the carriage-- which people were pushing and put the sick people on who couldn't walk-- whatever their condition was, respiratory ailment, cardiac problems.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the march was going on.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
